    "what_description": "Liquidambar cambodiana is a deciduous tree species native to Southeast Asia. It belongs to the family Altingiaceae, which comprises about 15 species of trees and shrubs. Botanically, Liquidambar cambodiana is characterized by its compound leaves, which are 15-30 cm long and have 5-7 leaflets that are ovate-lanceolate in shape and have a serrated margin. The tree can grow up to 20-30 meters tall, with a broad, rounded crown and a straight, cylindrical trunk. The bark is smooth and grey, with horizontal lenticels, and the flowers are small, yellowish-green and arranged in catkins.",
