    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Liquidambar cambodiana are liquidambar infusion, tincture, decoction, liquidambar tincture, and liquidambar tea. Liquidambar infusion is made by steeping the leaves in hot water, typically used to treat fever and rheumatism. Liquidambar tincture is a concentrated liquid extract obtained through the process of maceration or percolation, often used to treat digestive issues. Decoction is a method of extracting the medicinal properties of the bark, typically used to treat colds and coughs. Liquidambar tea is made by steeping the leaves in hot water and is often used to treat fever, headache, and skin conditions due to its antiseptic and antibacterial properties.",
